request.description:
This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve location information from the server. The request does not contain a request body. Upon a successful execution, the server responds with a status code of 200 and a JSON object containing a "success" key set to true, along with an array of "locations" objects. Each "locations" object contains an "_id" key and a nested "locations" array, which in turn contains "district" information.

